records.addlTxt: Motion and Order to Withdraw as Counsel filed by Atty Anne Renc (sent to Br 2 Judge on 10/04/21 sp)

Prosecuting District Attorney (DA) Louis John Molepske appeared for State of Wisconsin. Attorney  Anne Renc appeared by video for Defendant Brian A. Frazier. Defendant Brian A. Frazier not in court.
Cases heard at this time are 15CF-417 and 16CF-99.

10:33 AM Court calls cases.
Atty Molepske states appearances.

Defendant is not present. Defendant was released in April and Atty Renc is not sure where he is.
This is Defense's motion.

Court has read the submission.

Atty Renc addresses the Court as to the motion filed. State of Illiniois has failed to properly processed the request.
Atty Molepske addresses the Court, did not send a response because the motion was filed to Atty Jambois and has just reviewed this yesterday.
976.05 is referred to, Defendant failed to properly file under this statute. 
State vs. Blackburn (sp) is referred to. 

State did not lodge a detainer.
Atty Molepske addresses the Court further as to improper filing/mailing. 976.05(3)a. 
State does not have records that Defendant sent anything to the warden or District Attorney's office.
State vs. Smith is referred to.

State requests the Court to deny the motion.

Atty Renc addresses the Court, replies, requests Court to grant motion and dismiss these criminal complaints.

Court addresses the parties, states the facts for the record.

BY THE COURT:
Court denies motion. 

There are outstanding warrants on these cases. Execution on the warrants are abided by.

Atty Molepske addresses 15CF-133, which is not before the Court today. 
State has made an offer to Atty Renc to maybe resolve all this.  Defendant has been out of the facility since April 6, 2020.
State will file the appopriate pretrial forms. 

Court addresses parties further.

11:06 AM Matter has concluded.
Motion hearing on March 10, 2021 at 10:30 am.
